{
  "texts": [
    "Although analgesic medicines were considered important for CPLBP care, older people preferred care packages that extend beyond analgesia so that care is more holistic and considers safety (e.g.",
    "issues of dependency for opioid analgesics) and that were meaningful and personally enjoyable -such as social benefits of group exercise.",
    "Recent evidence points to the importance of considering pharmacologic and non-pharmacologic therapies for CPLBP care, consistent with the experiences, values and preferences of older people [97].",
    "Other evidence highlights care needs also extend beyond biomedical domains [24,103].",
    "Specifcally, tailoring components of care that addresses pain, emotional and social wellbeing, consistent with WHO ICOPE [101] model for improving functional ability, is important."
  ]
}